          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, season your <strong>basa </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Lay the <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> over the <strong>spinach & tomato orzo</strong>, top with the <strong>grated cheese</strong> and cook, covered, for 5 min or until the basa is cooked through – this is your <strong>one-pot creamy basa florentine</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily!</p>",
